<div style=3D"text-align: right;">b</div></th>
			<th scope=3D"col">&nbsp;</th>
			<th scope=3D"col">=20
<div>b / a</div></th>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">2</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">3</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:20px;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style=3D"width:100px;">1,5</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">3</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">5</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:20px;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style=3D"width:100px;">1,666666666...</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">5</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">8</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:20px;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style=3D"width:100px;">1,6</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">8</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">13</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:20px;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style=3D"width:100px;">1,625</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">...</div></td>
			<td>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">...</div></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>...</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">144</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">233</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:20px;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style=3D"width:100px;">1,618055556...</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">233</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:50px;">=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">377</div></td>
			<td style=3D"width:20px;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style=3D"width:100px;">1,618025751...</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">...</div></td>
			<td>=20
<div style=3D"text-align: right;">...</div></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>...</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
<p>Try some start values yourself:</p>=20

<iframe width=3D"798" height=3D"430" scrolling=3D"no" title=3D"JavaScript A=
nimation" style=3D"display: block; margin: auto; border: none; background-c=
olor: transparent; overflow: hidden; transition: 0.6s ease-in-out; max-widt=
h: 100%;"></iframe><div class=3D"script" style=3D"height: 430px; display: n=
one;">images/fibo.js</div>

<p>It can take longer to get good values, but it shows that not just the Fi=
bonacci Sequence can do this!</p>=20


<h2>Using The Golden Ratio to Calculate Fibonacci Numbers</h2>=20

<p>And even more surprising is that we can <b>calculate any Fibonacci Numbe=
r</b> using the Golden Ratio:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center larger">x<sub>n</sub> <em>=3D</em> <span class=3D"f"><u>=
=CF=86<sup>n</sup> =E2=88=92 (1=E2=88=92=CF=86)<sup>n</sup></u><em>=E2=88=
=9A5</em></span></p>=20
<p>The answer comes out <b>as a whole number</b>, exactly equal to the addi=
tion of the previous two terms.</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: x<sub>6</sub></h3>=20

	<p class=3D"center large">x<sub>6</sub> <em>=3D</em> <span class=3D"f"><u>=
(1,618034...)<sup>6</sup> =E2=88=92 (1=E2=88=921,618034...)<sup>6</sup></u>=
<em>=E2=88=9A5</em></span></p>=20
	<p>When I used a calculator on this (only entering the Golden Ratio to 6 d=
ecimal places) I got the answer <b>8,00000033</b> , a more accurate calcula=
tion would be closer to 8.</p>=20
	<p>Try n=3D12 and see what you get.</p>=20
</div>


<p>You can also calculate a Fibonacci Number by multiplying the previous Fi=
bonacci Number by the Golden Ratio and then rounding (works for numbers abo=
ve 1):</p>=20

<div class=3D"example">=20
	<h3>Example: What is the next in the sequence after 8 ?</h3>=20

	<p>It will be 8 times =CF=86:</p>=20
	<p class=3D"center">8=CF=86 <em>=3D</em> 8 =C3=97 1,618034...<br>
<em>=3D</em> 12,94427...<br>
<em>=3D</em> <b>13</b> (rounded)</p>=20
</div>=20


<h2>Some Interesting Things</h2>=20

<div class=3D"fun">=20

<h3>An odd fact:</h3>=20

<p>The sequence goes even, <b>odd</b>, <b>odd</b>, even, <b>odd</b>, <b>odd=
</b>, even, <b>odd</b>, <b>odd</b>, ... :</p>=20
<div class=3D"beach">

	<table class=3D"center">
		<tbody><tr>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;">0</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>1</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>1</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;">2</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>3</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>5</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;">8</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>13</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>21</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;">34</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>55</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>89</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;">144</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>233</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;"><b>377</b></td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;">610</td>
			<td style=3D"text-align:center; padding: 8px;">...</td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
</div>=20

<p>Why?</p>=20
<p>Because adding <b>two odd numbers produces an even number,</b> but addin=
g <b>even and odd (in any order) produces an odd number.<br></b></p>=20
</div><br>


<div class=3D"fun">=20

<h3>Lucas Numbers</h3>=20

<p>Starting the sequence with <b>2</b> and <b>1</b> we get the "Lucas Numbe=
rs". They get closer and closer to the powers (<a href=3D"https://www.maths=
isfun.com/exponent.html">exponents</a>) of the Golden Ratio:</p>=20
<div class=3D"simple">

