<p>There is an interesting pattern:</p>=20
<ul>=20
	<li>Look at the number <b>x<sub>3</sub> <em>=3D</em> 2</b>. Every <b>3</b>=
rd number is a multiple of <b>2</b> (2, 8, 34.144.610, ...)</li>=20
	<li>Look at the number <b>x<sub>4</sub> <em>=3D</em> 3</b>. Every <b>4</b>=
th number is a multiple of <b>3</b> (3, 21.144, ...)</li>=20
	<li>Look at the number <b>x<sub>5</sub> <em>=3D</em> 5</b>. Every <b>5</b>=
th number is a multiple of <b>5</b> (5, 55.610, ...)</li>=20
</ul>=20
<p>And so on (every <b>n</b>th number is a multiple of<b> x<sub>n</sub></b>=
).</p>=20
</div><br>


<div class=3D"fun">=20

